      "section": "Model Essay Basic",
      "tree": {
        "id": "root",
        "text": "Tomato and Egg Noodles Recipe (Basic Version)",
        "emoji": "🍜",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "b_prep",
            "text": "1. Preparation (准备食材)",
            "emoji": "🔪",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "b1",
                "text": "First, wash the tomatoes and cut them into small pieces. Also wash the vegetables.",
                "emoji": "🍅",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "b_base",
            "text": "2. Cooking the Base (炒底加水)",
            "emoji": "🥣",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "b2",
                "text": "Next, heat some oil in a pot and stir-fry the tomatoes with some salt.",
                "emoji": "🍳",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "b3",
                "text": "After one minute, pour three to four bowls of hot water into the pot.",
                "emoji": "🍲",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "b_cook",
            "text": "3. Cooking Noodles & Serving (煮面出锅)",
            "emoji": "🍜",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "b4",
                "text": "When the water boils, beat the eggs in and put in the noodles. Stir them for three minutes.",
                "emoji": "🥢",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "b5",
                "text": "Finally, add the vegetables and some salt, and boil for another three minutes. It is very simple to make!",
                "emoji": "😋",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "section": "Model Essay Advanced",
      "tree": {
        "id": "root",
        "text": "Tomato and Egg Noodles Recipe (Advanced Version)",
        "emoji": "✨",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "a_prep",
            "text": "1. Preparation (精致准备)",
            "emoji": "🔪",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "a1",
                "text": "First of all, prepare the ingredients by washing the fresh tomatoes and cutting them into delicate pieces, while keeping the green vegetables clean and set aside.",
                "highlight": "First of all, while",
                "emoji": "🍅",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "a_base",
            "text": "2. Cooking the Base (提鲜熬汤)",
            "emoji": "🥣",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "a2",
                "text": "Next, heat a tablespoon of cooking oil in a deep pot and stir-fry the tomato wedges with a pinch of salt to release their rich juice.",
                "highlight": "Next",
                "emoji": "🍳",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "a3",
                "text": "After about one minute, pour three to four bowls of hot water into the pot to create a savory soup base.",
                "highlight": "After about",
                "emoji": "🍲",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "a_cook",
            "text": "3. Cooking Noodles & Serving (精细烹煮)",
            "emoji": "🍜",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "a4",
                "text": "Once the water starts boiling, gently beat the eggs directly into the soup, add the noodles, and stir carefully for three minutes to prevent sticking.",
                "highlight": "Once, directly",
                "emoji": "🥢",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "a5",
                "text": "Finally, add the green vegetables and adjust the seasoning with another pinch of salt, boiling everything for another three minutes before serving this incredibly delicious meal.",
                "highlight": "Finally, before",
                "emoji": "😋",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
